class Solution {
    public int canBeTypedWords(String text, String brokenLetters) {
        boolean[] broken = new boolean[26];
        for (char c : brokenLetters.toCharArray()) {
            broken[c - 'a'] = true;
        }
        int count = 0;
        for (String word : text.split(" ")) {
            boolean ok = true;
            for (char c : word.toCharArray()) {
                if (broken[c - 'a']) {
                    ok = false;
                    break;
                }
            }
            if (ok) count++;
        }
        return count;
    }
}
```
efficiency: HIGH
time complexity: O(N + M)
space complexity: O(1)
energy implications: LOW
explanation: Uses a boolean array to mark broken letters for O(1) lookup. Splits the text into words and checks each character in each word against the broken set. Early-exit on first broken character minimizes work.

